Package: LDna
Type: Package
Title: Linkage disequilibrum network analysis (LDna)
Version: 0.57
Date: 2014-03-19
Author: Petri Kemppainen <petrikemppainen2@gmail.com>
Maintainer:  Petri Kemppainen <petrikemppainen2@gmail.com>
Depends: R (>= 3.0.2), ape, igraph, parallel
Imports: ape, igraph
Description: Performs linkage disequilibrium networks analyses (LDna). In LD networks
            nodes represent loci and connections between nodes represent LD values
            above a given threshold. Distinct clusters visible across a wide range
            of LD thresholds are likely to be associated with distinct evolutionary
            events or forces. By monitoring change in LD as clusters successively
            merge with decreasing LD threshold, such distinct clusters can be
            identified and extracted at appropriate LD thresholds. Cluster merging
            is visualized using trees, where represent  clusters and node distance
            clusters and distance indicates at LD threshold at which this occurrs. 
            Functions are provided to: produce necessary data files for LDna from a 
            matrix of pairwise LD values; calculate lambda, which measured the change 
            in LD before and after cluster merging and is used to identify distinct 
            clusters; extract clusters based on user defined parameters; summerize 
            data and visualise results, both when extracting clusers and when 
            exploring the extracted clusters.
